# Accessibility Guidelines

## ARIA and Semantic HTML
- Include proper ARIA attributes where needed
- Use semantic HTML elements (header, main, section, etc.)
- Provide proper labels for form inputs
- Use heading hierarchy correctly (h1, h2, h3, etc.)

## Keyboard Navigation
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Implement proper focus management
- Use proper tab order for form elements
- Handle keyboard events appropriately

## Radix UI Integration
- Follow Radix UI accessibility patterns
- Use Radix components which have built-in accessibility
- Leverage Radix's keyboard navigation features
- Follow Radix documentation for proper usage

## Visual Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Provide alternative text for images
- Use focus indicators for interactive elements

## Screen Reader Support
- Test with screen readers when possible
- Use proper ARIA labels and descriptions
- Implement skip links for navigation
- Provide text alternatives for visual content
